# Fixture Generation Script

The file [fixtures/generate.py](mdc:fixtures/generate.py) generates a sample Python project under `fixtures/sample_project/` for testing ouroboros.

## When to update

Whenever a new feature is added to ouroboros-core or ouroboros-cli that changes what inputs the tool expects from a project (config files, directory layout, file conventions, etc.), the generate script must be updated so the sample project exercises the new feature.

Examples of changes that require an update:

- New keys added to the `oboros.toml` config schema ([config.rs](mdc:crates/ouroboros-core/src/config.rs))
- New file types scanned (e.g. `.pyi` support)
- New directory conventions (e.g. namespace packages, test directories)
- New exclude/include patterns

## How the script works

- `BASE_FILES` dict defines the hand-crafted ~30 file skeleton
- `_generate_scaled_files()` procedurally adds more files when `--scale > 1`
- The `generate()` function writes all files plus `oboros.toml` into `fixtures/sample_project/`
- The `oboros.toml` config is written at the end of `generate()` and should reflect the current config schema
